# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.

## Scope and source of truth

This project is the **Investment Tools main project** (GitHub: `martin1dlouhy/Main-Project`, deployed at https://main-five-alpha.vercel.app).

The workspace-level `CLAUDE.md` at `../../CLAUDE.md` is canonical for the **hard rules** (no writes to browser storage, no OneDrive access, preserve backwards compatibility, never `git push` automatically, Czech responses to Martin, Kritik auto-review). Read it — do not duplicate its rules here.

This file covers only what is specific to operating inside this directory.

## Commands

There is **no build step, no lint, no tests**. The frontend is pure static files served as-is. Correctness comes from manual browser walkthroughs + the `critic` skill's Kritik review.

```bash
# Run the Railway backend locally (requires env vars listed below)
cd railway-api && npm install && npm start          # serves on :3001

# Deploy frontend (run from this directory, only when Martin asks)
git add . && git commit -m "..." && git push origin main
# Vercel auto-deploys ~30s after push. Railway auto-deploys its own repo on push.
```

Serve the frontend locally with any static server (e.g. `npx serve .`) — there is no dev server script. When testing apps that call the Railway backend, point their fetch URLs at `http://localhost:3001` or ensure the local origin (`http://localhost:3000` / `:8080` / `127.0.0.1:*`) is in the CORS allowlist in `railway-api/server.js`.

## Architecture — the things that need multiple files to see

### Single-file apps, shared shell

Each app is **one self-contained HTML file** with inline `<style>` and `<script>` — typically 700–5,300 lines. Only the outer shell is shared: `styles.css` (CSS variables + nav + footer) and `script.js` (theme toggle). Resist extracting shared modules; self-containment is intentional.

When creating a new app, copy `APP-TEMPLATE.html` and **do not modify** `.top-nav`, `.footer`, or the theme-switch wiring. Always use `var(--accent)` etc. — never hardcode hex.

### Dual backend (by timeout)

Two backends exist because Vercel serverless caps at 60 s:

- `api/*.js` — **Vercel serverless** (Node). `sp500.js` scrapes SlickCharts via Cheerio and sets a 24 h CDN cache (`s-maxage=86400`). `parse-lv.js` is the 60 s-capped Claude LV parser. `ares.js` does ARES company lookup (15 s). Timeouts are configured in `vercel.json`.
- `railway-api/server.js` — **Railway Express** (Node ≥18, single file). Hosts everything that can exceed 60 s or needs secrets: `/api/verify-pin` (SHA-256 vs `PIN_HASH` env, in-memory rate limit 5 attempts / 5 min / IP), `/api/parse-lv` (no-timeout Claude version), `/api/generate-loan-doc` (Claude-driven DOCX fill), `/api/marketing/generate` (OpenAI text), `/api/marketing/generate-image` (DALL-E / gpt-image-1).

**CORS on Railway is a strict allowlist** (`allowedOrigins` array near the top of `railway-api/server.js`). Adding a new frontend origin — including any new Vercel preview domain or local port — requires editing that array.

Required Railway env vars: `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `GEMINI_API_KEY`, `PIN_HASH`, optional `PORT` (default 3001).

### Theme system

Toggling light/dark switches the `.carbon` class on both `<html>` and `<body>`, persisted to `localStorage["daynight-theme"]` as `"snow"` or `"carbon"`. Full token list in `DESIGN-SYSTEM.md`. The hard rule: **never write to `localStorage` / `sessionStorage` / IndexedDB from your tooling** — Real Estate Prompt Generator and Term Sheet store real user data there.

### Data storage in apps (do not touch without explicit instruction)

- `real-estate-prompt-generator.html` uses a 3-tier scheme: `localStorage` + `IndexedDB` + the File System Access API to mirror into a user-chosen local folder (NOT OneDrive).
- `termsheet-generator.html` is PIN-gated and keeps saved Term Sheets in `localStorage`.
- `marketing-agent.html` syncs generated output to a user-selected Google Drive folder via `google-drive-sync.js`.

## App inventory (quick map)

LIVE (do not break): `debt-calculator.html`, `real-estate-prompt-generator.html` (largest, ~5.3k lines, 6-step wizard), `sp500-calculator.html`, `termsheet-generator.html` (PIN-gated), `loan-documentation.html`.
Active dev: `marketing-agent.html`.
WIP: `portfolio-dashboard.html`, `portfolio-preview.html` (v3 iteration, Chart.js).

`INVESTMENT-TOOLS-OVERVIEW.md` has the full per-app breakdown — open it before touching an unfamiliar app.

## Planning vs. doing

For non-trivial edits enter plan mode first, propose, wait for approval, then implement. Typo fixes and one-line tweaks can go straight through. Do not change code unrelated to the current task.
